answers.body_markdown:
Simple! ReactHtmlParser() returns an HTML element object, and textarea expects plain text as its value. I&#39;m guessing you are trying to build an HTML editor. Then you have to use it as below:

    &lt;textarea
      className=&quot;form-control&quot;
      aria-label=&quot;With textarea&quot;
      placeholder=&quot;Remark&quot;
      name=&quot;Remarks&quot;
      value={this.state.Remarks}
      onChange={this.handleChange}
    &gt;&lt;/textarea&gt;

and the handle change:

    handleChange = (event)=&gt;{
        this.setState({
            Remarks: event.target.value
        })
    }

then at preview/view :

    &lt;div&gt; { ReactHtmlParser(this.state.Remarks) } &lt;/div&gt;

`Textarea` is showing the value [object Object] correctly.

`ReactHtmlParser(this.state.Remarks)` returns object which when converted to string gives us `[object Object]`.

The correct use would be to put html inside the `textarea` and render it elsewhere.

Working code here:-

    import React from &quot;react&quot;;
    import ReactDOM from &quot;react-dom&quot;;
    import ReactHtmlParser from &quot;react-html-parser&quot;;
    
    class App extends React.Component {
      state = {
        Remarks: `&lt;div&gt;Hi, 
        &lt;button&gt;My Button&lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;`
      };
      handleChange = ({ target }) =&gt; {
        this.setState({
          [target.name]: target.value
        });
      };
      render() {
        return (
          &lt;div className=&quot;App&quot;&gt;
            &lt;textarea
              className=&quot;form-control&quot;
              aria-label=&quot;With textarea&quot;
              placeholder=&quot;Remark&quot;
              name=&quot;Remarks&quot;
              value={this.state.Remarks}
              onChange={this.handleChange}
            /&gt;
            {ReactHtmlParser(this.state.Remarks)}
          &lt;/div&gt;
        );
      }
    }
    
    const rootElement = document.getElementById(&quot;root&quot;);
    ReactDOM.render(&lt;App /&gt;, rootElement);

